  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 55fc01baa0be7b54e8ef6801bfc93ce6, type: 3}
  m_Name: BadEnding
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  PromptOneButtonDisplay: 0
  PromptTwoButtonDisplay: 0
  ButtonOneText: 
  ButtonTwoText: 
  NormalDialogue:
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Does your death, caused by your hands, satisfy you?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: If you ever shot yourself, you witnessed death before coming back to
      life.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Why, after witnessing it at least once, did you want to fully exit this
      world?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Did it feel nice being dead for those few seconds, like everything just
      cut out as if you were in a movie?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Did death really appease you?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: I've seen so many other black sheep like you who chose to kill themselves
      in front of me. It sucks that the dead can't answer my questions.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: "You all walked down the same self-destructive path\u2026"
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Maybe after seeing death up close, it could have allowed you to understand
      yourself a little better.
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Will this be the last time I see you, or will we repeat this encounter?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Will your choices be the same in the next cycle? Do your choices really
      matter if we're going to go through this same torment?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: Will you make new choices?
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: "You paid the price in the form of bodily harm. You\u2019ve always paid
      a price."
  - CharacterTitle: 1
    Message: "You lost everything, and I won everything. Such is the nature of casinos\u2026"
  ButtonOneDialogue: []
  ButtonTwoDialogue: []
